recommendations for a page turner i haven't been into reading for awhile and i think a good way to get back into it is with a good suspense novel some pop lit nothing too deep right now but something that is a good page turner any recommendations i don't like a lot of gore or books with a high body count i would be interested in a conspiracy thriller ludlum esque a good spy story anything by harlen coben his books are a quick easy read because it is too hard to put them down once you've started reading it they keep you on the edge waiting to see what is coming next his books are stories of suspence and intrigue with his characters often crossing over from book to book just when you think you have outwitted coben and figured out who dunnit he throws you another curve and you are left sitting with your mouth agape as you read yet another twist to the plot i guarantee that any one of his books will be just what you are looking for some of his titles the woods his latest deal breaker tell no one gone for good no second chance just one look the innocent promise me i'm sure you can find his works in your local library or bookstore happy reading Spy fiction The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Aerial (dance move) Theory of conduct Thriller Skateboarding trick Literature Crime film Book Tina Turner Equine conformation Airport novel The Amber Spyglass Professional wrestling throws The Pilgrim's Progress Volleyball Drill bit Tag Mattress Daredevil Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Legal research Crime fiction Charmed Genre fiction The Catcher in the Rye Professional wrestling holds Normal distribution Professional wrestling double-team maneuvers Plame affair Indiana Jones and the Infernal Machine Professional wrestling attacks Knife Saw II Knots Landing Milton H. Erickson Piccolo Junior Saga Diving Swingout Pitaten Car handling Carl Barks Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Science fiction on television Extreme Programming Gollum Ken Grimwood Alfred Hitchcock Sheepshead No